ration officials said in&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gsa.gov/about-us/newsroom/news-releases/president-biden-and-us-general-services-administration-announce-major-land-port-projects-funded-by-bipartisan-infrastructure-law-02252022" target="_blank" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; outline: 0px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 45, 108); cursor: pointer; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 1px dotted rgb(0, 45, 108); border-left: none; border-image: initial; padding-bottom: 2px;">announcing the funding plan</a>&nbsp;last month. The $3.4 billion investment comes from the bipartisan infrastructure law.</p><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Delays and long lines at land ports of entry are common, especially at the nation's highest trafficked regions, like San Diego. On the southern border alone, delays have cost 88,000 jobs and roughly $3 billion in economic output, according to&nbsp;<a href="https://www.sandag.org/uploads/committeeid/borders_committee.pdf" target="_blank" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; outline: 0px; line-height: 28px; color: rgb(0, 45, 108); cursor: pointer; border-top: none; border-right: none; border-bottom: 1px dotted rgb(0, 45, 108); border-left: none; border-image: initial; padding-bottom: 2px;">a 2016 study</a>&nbsp;of cross-border trade.</p><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">"Those inefficiencies translate into a weaker economy, fewer jobs and we can do better," U.S. General Services Administrator Robin Carnahan told reporters at an event announcing the border funding. "A lot of these land ports are beyond their useful life and their capacity in many ways and these upgrades that we're talking about today are long overdue."</p><div style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div class="ResponsiveWrapper" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box;"><aside class="InlineElement InlineElement--content-width InlineElement--desktop InlineImage" aria-label="Image" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; margin: 24px auto; clear: both;"><div class="ScrollSpy_container" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"></span></div><figure class="Image aspect-ratio--parent InlineImage--image" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; display: block; height: auto; overflow: hidden; position: relative; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%;"><div class="RatioFrame aspect-ratio--auto" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; overflow: hidden;"></div><div class="Image__Wrapper Image__Wrapper--relative" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; z-index: 1; position: relative;"><picture style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"><source srcset="https://s.abcnews.com/images/International/mexico-border-gty-jt-220329_1648598940969_hpEmbed_2_22x15_608.jpg" media="(max-width: 767px)" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-s