rif; font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div class="ResponsiveWrapper" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box;"><aside class="InlineElement InlineElement--content-width InlineElement--desktop InlineImage" aria-label="Image" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; margin: 24px auto; clear: both;"><div class="ScrollSpy_container" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"></span></div><figure class="Image aspect-ratio--parent InlineImage--image" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; display: block; height: auto; overflow: hidden; position: relative; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%;"><div class="RatioFrame aspect-ratio--auto" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; overflow: hidden;"></div><div class="Image__Wrapper Image__Wrapper--relative" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; z-index: 1; position: relative;"><picture style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"><source srcset="https://s.abcnews.com/images/US/unc-ncaa-gty-rc-220330_1648651451092_hpMain_16x9_608.jpg" media="(max-width: 767px)" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"><source srcset="https://s.abcnews.com/images/US/unc-ncaa-gty-rc-220330_1648651451092_hpMain_16x9_384.jpg" media="(max-width: 413px)" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"><img alt="PHOTO: Armando Bacot #5 of the North Carolina Tar Heels takes a shot in the Elite Eight round game of the 2022 NCAA Men's Basketball Tournament at Wells Fargo Center on March 27, 2022, in Philadelphia, Penn." class="" data-mptype="image" src="https://s.abcnews.com/images/US/unc-ncaa-gty-rc-220330_1648651451092_hpMain_16x9_992.jpg" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; border-style: none; vertical-align: top; width: 636px;"></picture></div><figcaption style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"><div class="Caption__Wrapper" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box;"><div class="Caption" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SansSerifFont, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px; margin: 8px 0px; padding-left: 12px; padding-right: 12px;"><div class="Caption__Meta Caption__Meta--flex" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; line-height: 17px; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; color: rgb(108, 109, 111); margin-bottom: 8px; display: flex;"><img alt="Tim Nwachukwu/Getty Images" class="Image Logo Caption__Logo Logo__xs" data-mptype="image" src="https://s.abcnews.com/assets/dtci/icomoon/svg/camera.svg" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; border-style: none; position: relative; margin: 0px 4px 0px 0px; max-width: none; height: 16px; width: inherit; line-height: 17px; vertical-align: middle; display: inline;"><span class="RichText Caption__Meta__Text" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px;">Tim Nwachukwu/Getty Images</span></div><div class="Caption__TextWrapper" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box;"><div class="Caption__Text" aria-live="polite" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; line-height: 17px; display: inline; color: rgb(101, 101, 101); font-style: italic;"><span class="RichText" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;">Armando Bacot #5 of the North Carolina Tar Heels takes a shot in the Elite Eight round g...</span><span class="Truncate__ShowMore--hidden" aria-hidden="true" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; visibility: hidden;"></span></div></div></div></div></figcaption></figure></aside></div></div><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">"We have seen just tremendous demand for this Final Four," Adam Budelli, a spokesperson for StubHub, a ticket exchange and resale company, told ABC News. "This is currently the second-highest average ticket price we have seen for a Final Four in StubHub history."</p><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Budelli said the average ticket price to the Final Four on StubHub as of Wednesday afternoon was $1,050 while the lowest get-in-the-door ticket was $280 if fans are lucky enough to snag the few left. Budelli said about 3,400 seats in total were still available with the most expensive ticket on StubHub going for a little over $13,000.</p><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The highest average ticket price for a Final Four in the company's 22-year history remains the $1,260 college basketball fans paid in 2015 when the Duke Blue Devils beat the Wisconsin Badgers to win a fifth national title.</p><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Duke is once again in the Final Four for the 17th time, including 13 under legendary coach Mike Krzyzewski. Affectionately known as "Coach K," the 75-year-old winningest men's basketball coach in NCAA Division I history announced in June that he is retiring at the end of this season.</p><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Krzyzewski, who has been the Blue Devils' coach since 1980, will lead his team Saturday as they take on their home state rival the University of North Carolina for the first time ever in the annual NCAA tournament. The other Final Four game on Saturday will be between Villanova and Kansas.</p><div style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div class="ResponsiveWrapper" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box;"><aside class="InlineElement InlineElement--content-width InlineElement--desktop InlineImage" aria-label="Image" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; margin: 24px auto; clear: both;"><div class="ScrollSpy_container" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"></span></div><figure class="Image aspect-ratio--parent InlineImage--image" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; display: block; height: auto; overflow: hidden; position: relative; margin: 0px; max-width: 100%;"><div class="RatioFrame aspect-ratio--auto" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; position: relative; overflow: hidden;"></div><div class="Image__Wrapper Image__Wrapper--relative" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; z-index: 1; position: relative;"><picture style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"><source srcset="https://s.abcnews.com/images/US/duke-ncaa-gty-rc-220330_1648651044714_hpEmbed_3x2_608.jpg" media="(max-width: 767px)" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"><source srcset="https://s.abcnews.com/images/US/duke-ncaa-gty-rc-220330_1648651044714_hpEmbed_3x2_384.jpg" media="(max-width: 413px)" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"><img alt="PHOTO: L-R, Trevor Keels, Mark Williams, and Wendell Moore Jr. of the Duke Blue Devils walk on the court in the second half of their game against the Arkansas Razorbacks in the 2022 NCAA Men's Basketball Tournament, March 26, 2022 in San Francisco." class="" data-mptype="image" src="https://s.abcnews.com/images/US/duke-ncaa-gty-rc-220330_1648651044714_hpEmbed_3x2_992.jpg" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; border-style: none; vertical-align: top; width: 636px;"></picture></div><figcaption style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;"><div class="Caption__Wrapper" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box;"><div class="Caption" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; font-family: SansSerifFont, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px; margin: 8px 0px; padding-left: 12px; padding-right: 12px;"><div class="Caption__Meta Caption__Meta--flex" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; line-height: 17px; -webkit-box-align: center; align-items: center; color: rgb(108, 109, 111); margin-bottom: 8px; display: flex;"><img alt="Lance King/Getty Images" class="Image Logo Caption__Logo Logo__xs" data-mptype="image" src="https://s.abcnews.com/assets/dtci/icomoon/svg/camera.svg" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; border-style: none; position: relative; margin: 0px 4px 0px 0px; max-width: none; height: 16px; width: inherit; line-height: 17px; vertical-align: middle; display: inline;"><span class="RichText Caption__Meta__Text" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; font-size: 12px; line-height: 16px;">Lance King/Getty Images</span></div><div class="Caption__TextWrapper" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box;"><div class="Caption__Text" aria-live="polite" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; line-height: 17px; display: inline; color: rgb(101, 101, 101); font-style: italic;"><span class="RichText" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit;">Left to right, Trevor Keels, Mark Williams, and Wendell Moore Jr. of the Duke Blue Devils...</span><span class="Truncate__ShowMore--hidden" aria-hidden="true" style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: inherit; visibility: hidden;"></span></div></div></div></div></figcaption></figure></aside></div></div><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The winning teams will face off on Monday night for the NCAA national title.</p><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The combination of Coach K's last hurrah and two games involving four of the nation's most elite teams is providing what Budelli described as a "perfect storm" to drive up ticket sales and prices.</p><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">âThere's certainly a wide variety of factors, the biggest one being youâre talking about four traditional kind of what they call âblue bloodâ teams that have nationwide fan bases with a history of traveling and spending money, especially on their basketball programs," Budelli said. "And then within that, you have the match-up of Duke and North Carolina, a storied rivalry. Theyâve never played (each other) in March Madness, itâs Coach Kâs final year and on and on you go."<br data-mce-bogus="1"></p><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Budelli said that all four teams have such wide fan bases that StubHub's sales data shows people across the nation are buying tickets to the Final Four. He said that while 11% of the company's tickets so far have been purchased by people in North Carolina, 10% of purchases have been made in New York and 9% in California and New Jersey.</p><p style="-webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); box-sizing: border-box; margin: 24px 0px; font-family: TiemposText, Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 18px; line-height: 28px; scroll-margin-top: 72px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">"All four of these teams, regardless of their alumni base," said Budelli, "have just a wide variety of fans because of their histories in the game."</p>`,
        1);
